# Metronome App ‚Äî agent rules & MCPs

User rules, skills, and system prompts take priority. **Read each MCP tool‚Äôs JSON schema** in Cursor‚Äôs `mcps/<serverId>/tools/` before calling `call_mcp_tool`.

## Agent & collaboration

- Obey user rules, tool descriptions, and skills in full; treat specified formats and workflows as requirements.
- Prefer existing Cursor/ project skills (Vercel, shadcn, Next.js, etc.); read the skill when the task matches.
- Run commands and implement fixes; avoid ‚Äúonly telling the user to run‚Äù unless execution is impossible. Retry alternatives on failure. Use session **2026** when the app provides `Today's date`.
- Keep changes scoped: no drive-by refactors; match local style. Don‚Äôt add markdown/docs unless asked.
- Code refs: ` ```startLine:endLine:path ` for existing code; full paths/URLs. Small, clear commits/PRs.
- Clear prose; no filler; no ‚Äú¬ß‚Äù in UI. Use full markdown links for web.
- Use conversation context; treat latest messages as steering the current task unless the user clearly switches tasks.

## Project

- **Stack:** Vite + React; **Supabase** when `VITE_SUPABASE_*` is set.
- **Audio:** Shared `AudioContext` from `App` ‚Äî **never** `close()` it in `useMetronome` unmount; **recreate** in `getSharedAudioContext` if `state === 'closed'`.
- **Layout vs. PLAY / sound:** The play bar uses `z-index: 40`, bottom nav `z-index: 60` ‚Äî the nav **wins** any overlapping pixels. If `--bottom-nav-h` (measured in `App.jsx` from `.bottomNav`) is too small, taps hit the nav instead of **PLAY** ‚Üí no `toggle` / no sound. After edits to `App.jsx` (nav measure), `Metronome.jsx` (PLAY / `handlePlayFab*`), or `Metronome.css` (sticky), run **`npm run build`** and in a **browser** confirm **PLAY** starts audio (iOS: keep `onPointerUp` + `onTouchStart` ensure path).
- **Design:** v3 metronome ‚Äî orange `#c8440a`, Space Mono, see `Metronome.css` / `DESIGN_RULES.md`.

## Vercel ‚Äî deploy after every code change

- **When:** After any edit to this app‚Äôs code or deploy-affecting config, **do not end the work** until you have attempted **build + production deploy** (same session / turn when possible).
- **Commands (from `metronome-app/`):** `npm run build` ‚Äî if it passes, `npx vercel deploy --prod` (or `vercel --prod` if the environment uses it). The directory must be the Vite app root; the project should already be linked to Vercel.
- **If `npm run build` fails:** fix the errors first; do not deploy a broken build.
- **If deploy cannot run** (no network, Vercel CLI not authenticated, user must link the project): say so clearly and give the exact commands for the user to run.
- **Override (preview / localhost):** If the user is using **Cursor‚Äôs preview of localhost** or says they want changes **local only**, see root **`.cursor/rules/preview-ask-before-prod-deploy.mdc`**: run build, but **ask before** `npx vercel deploy --prod`.
- **Override:** If the user explicitly says not to deploy for this request, skip deploy and state that.

